19#include <sys/types.h>
20
21#include <stdlib.h>
22#include <string.h>
23
24#include "tmux.h"
25
26/*
27 * Send keys to client.
28 */
29
30static enum cmd_retval cmd_send_keys_exec(struct cmd *, struct cmdq_item *);
31
32const struct cmd_entry cmd_send_keys_entry = {
33 .name = "send-keys",
34 .alias = "send",
35
36 .args = { "lXRMN:t:", 0, -1 },
37 .usage = "[-lXRM] [-N repeat-count] " CMD_TARGET_PANE_USAGE " key ...",
38
39 .target = { 't', CMD_FIND_PANE, 0 },
40
41 .flags = CMD_AFTERHOOK,
42 .exec = cmd_send_keys_exec
43};
44
45const struct cmd_entry cmd_send_prefix_entry = {
46 .name = "send-prefix",
47 .alias = NULL,
48
49 .args = { "2t:", 0, 0 },
50 .usage = "[-2] " CMD_TARGET_PANE_USAGE,
51
52 .target = { 't', CMD_FIND_PANE, 0 },
53
54 .flags = CMD_AFTERHOOK,
55 .exec = cmd_send_keys_exec
56};
57
58static void
59cmd_send_keys_inject(struct client *c, struct cmdq_item *item, key_code key)
60{
61 struct window_pane *wp = item->target.wp;
62 struct session *s = item->target.s;
63 struct key_table *table;
64 struct key_binding *bd;
65
66 if (wp->mode == NULL || wp->mode->key_table == NULL) {
67 if (options_get_number(wp->window->options, "xterm-keys"))
68 key |= KEYC_XTERM;
69 window_pane_key(wp, NULL, s, key, NULL);
70 return;
71 }
72 table = key_bindings_get_table(wp->mode->key_table(wp), 1);
73
74 bd = key_bindings_get(table, key & ~KEYC_XTERM);
75 if (bd != NULL) {
76 table->references++;
77 key_bindings_dispatch(bd, item, c, NULL, &item->target);
78 key_bindings_unref_table(table);
79 }
80}
81
82static enum cmd_retval
83cmd_send_keys_exec(struct cmd *self, struct cmdq_item *item)
84{
85 struct args *args = self->args;
86 struct client *c = cmd_find_client(item, NULL, 1);
87 struct window_pane *wp = item->target.wp;
88 struct session *s = item->target.s;
89 struct mouse_event *m = &item->shared->mouse;
90 struct utf8_data *ud, *uc;
91 wchar_t wc;
92 int i, literal;
93 key_code key;
94 u_int np = 1;
95 char *cause = NULL;
96
97 if (args_has(args, 'N')) {
98 np = args_strtonum(args, 'N', 1, UINT_MAX, &cause);
99 if (cause != NULL) {
100 cmdq_error(item, "repeat count %s", cause);
101 free(cause);
102 return (CMD_RETURN_ERROR);
103 }
104 if (args_has(args, 'X') || args->argc == 0)
105 wp->modeprefix = np;
106 }
107
108 if (args_has(args, 'X')) {
109 if (wp->mode == NULL || wp->mode->command == NULL) {
110 cmdq_error(item, "not in a mode");
111 return (CMD_RETURN_ERROR);
112 }
113 if (!m->valid)
114 wp->mode->command(wp, c, s, args, NULL);
115 else
116 wp->mode->command(wp, c, s, args, m);
117 return (CMD_RETURN_NORMAL);
118 }
119
120 if (args_has(args, 'M')) {
121 wp = cmd_mouse_pane(m, &s, NULL);
122 if (wp == NULL) {
123 cmdq_error(item, "no mouse target");
124 return (CMD_RETURN_ERROR);
125 }
126 window_pane_key(wp, NULL, s, m->key, m);
127 return (CMD_RETURN_NORMAL);
128 }
129
130 if (self->entry == &cmd_send_prefix_entry) {
131 if (args_has(args, '2'))
132 key = options_get_number(s->options, "prefix2");
133 else
134 key = options_get_number(s->options, "prefix");
135 cmd_send_keys_inject(c, item, key);
136 return (CMD_RETURN_NORMAL);
137 }
138
139 if (args_has(args, 'R')) {
140 window_pane_reset_palette(wp);
141 input_reset(wp, 1);
142 }
143
144 for (; np != 0; np--) {
145 for (i = 0; i < args->argc; i++) {
146 literal = args_has(args, 'l');
147 if (!literal) {
148 key = key_string_lookup_string(args->argv[i]);
149 if (key != KEYC_NONE && key != KEYC_UNKNOWN)
150 cmd_send_keys_inject(c, item, key);
151 else
152 literal = 1;
153 }
154 if (literal) {
155 ud = utf8_fromcstr(args->argv[i]);
156 for (uc = ud; uc->size != 0; uc++) {
157 if (utf8_combine(uc, &wc) != UTF8_DONE)
158 continue;
159 cmd_send_keys_inject(c, item, wc);
160 }
161 free(ud);
162 }
163 }
164
165 }
166
167 return (CMD_RETURN_NORMAL);
168}
